  "local_port": 54504,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why does my DIRECTV guide read \"to be announced\"?",
  "response": "The \"To Be Announced\" (TBA) message on your DIRECTV guide usually appears when the network or channel has not yet provided information about the programming for that particular time slot. This can happen for a variety of reasons:\n\n1. **Last-Minute Changes**: Sometimes, networks make last-minute changes to their schedules, and the updated information might not have been sent to DIRECTV yet.\n\n2. **New Shows or Specials**: If a channel is planning to air a new show, special event, or movie, the details might not be finalized until closer to the air date.\n\n3. **Scheduling Delays**: There might be delays in the scheduling process, causing a temporary TBA listing.\n\n4. **Technical Issues**: Occasionally, technical glitches can prevent the guide data from being updated properly.\n\nTo resolve this, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. **Refresh Your Guide**: You can manually refresh your DIRECTV guide by pressing the \"Guide\" button on your remote, then navigating to \"Settings,\" and selecting \"Refresh Guide Data.\" This can help pull in the latest programming information.\n\n2. **Wait It Out**: Often, the TBA listing will be updated automatically as the network finalizes its schedule. Checking back later might show the updated programming.\n\n3. **Check Online**: Sometimes, visiting the network's official website or checking their social media channels can give you more up-to-date information about their programming schedule.\n\nIf the issue persists and you're unable to get any updated information, you might want to contact DIRECTV customer support for further assistance.",
